ty in promoting and sustaining behaviour change in the UK. Given the negative outcomes that welfare conditionality routinely triggers, this book calls for the abandonment of these sanctions and reiterates the importance of genuinely supportive policies that promote social security and wider equality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aPublic welfarexMoral and ethical aspects. 0aPublic welfare. 0aWelfare recipients. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aB.R. Stewart, Alasdair, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJones, Katy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aScullion, Lisa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831111967700 cprintz978144734373840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447343721423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447343721/original  a978-3-11-119677-0  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles